2 formats of connection Strings :-
  1) Standard Format: It is used to connect standaklone clusters, replica sets, or sharded clusters
  2) DNS Seed List format: provides a dns server server list to our connection string 
                           gives more flexibility of deployment
                           ability to change servers in rotation without configuring clients

CONNECTION STRING : mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0.usqsf.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority
